      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CHARGE AHEAD (5) is racing in fine form and made it two wins in a row last week when he led and fought well to get the cash by a head at this circuit and distance. Draws wider but won from this barrier prior. Can land the hat trick. COOL NIGHT (3) was only 3.5 metres behind CHARGE AHEAD last week and came from this barrier when winning at this circuit and distance last month. Expect him to be prominent. OUR SUNSET DELIGHT (2) resumes following a layoff of four-and-a-half months but generally comes to hand very quickly with four wins and two placings from eight first-up appearances. Should enjoy a nice run from this favourable starting position. Expecting a bright start to the campaign. MIRACLE MOOSE NZ (1) will be cherry-ripe after four runs back from a spell. Hasn't been far away at his last couple and draws to advantage.",
